casebody.data:
HAROLD E. GRIEST v. MARY KELLY GRIEST. [No. 87,

October Term, 1927.]

Decided February 2nd, 1928.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Pattison, Ubneb, Adkins, Oeeutt, Digges, Pabke, and Sloan, JJ.

Frederick Lee Cobourn, for the appellant. Robert H. Archer, for the appellee. Adkins, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court, affirming the decree, with costs to the appellee.
